@startuml
title Participant Join and Geolocation
hide footbox
autonumber

skinparam BackgroundColor transparent
skinparam SequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam MaxMessageSize 110
skinparam WrapWidth 220
skinparam RoundCorner 8

actor "Participant browser\nstatic/participant.js" as Participant
participant "Railway HTTP proxy" as RailwayHTTP
participant "Daemon participant router\n/api/participant/*" as ParticipantAPI
participant "Railway session WS\nfeatures/ws/router.py" as RailwayWS
participant "Host browser\nparticipant list / map" as Host

Participant -> RailwayHTTP: POST /{session}/api/participant/register\nX-Participant-ID: uuid
RailwayHTTP -> ParticipantAPI: proxy register request

alt Returning UUID
  ParticipantAPI -> ParticipantAPI: reuse stored name + avatar
else First time in this session
  ParticipantAPI -> ParticipantAPI: assign workshop/conference name\nassign avatar\ninitialize score
  ParticipantAPI -> Host: notify_host(updated participant list)
end

ParticipantAPI --> RailwayHTTP: {name, avatar}
RailwayHTTP --> Participant: assigned identity

Participant -> RailwayWS: connect /ws/{session_id}/{uuid}
RailwayWS -> RailwayWS: validate active session_id
RailwayWS -> RailwayWS: store socket + participant IP
RailwayWS -> Host: broadcast participant presence update
RailwayWS --> Participant: WS open

Participant -> RailwayHTTP: GET /{session}/api/participant/state
RailwayHTTP -> ParticipantAPI: proxy state request
ParticipantAPI --> RailwayHTTP: personalized state snapshot
RailwayHTTP --> Participant: state + activity + score + slides

Participant -> RailwayHTTP: POST /{session}/api/participant/location\nstored GPS or timezone fallback
RailwayHTTP -> ParticipantAPI: proxy location update
ParticipantAPI -> ParticipantAPI: save participant_state.locations[uuid]
ParticipantAPI -> Host: notify_host(updated participant list)
ParticipantAPI --> RailwayHTTP: 204

opt User accepts browser geolocation later
  Participant -> Participant: navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition()
  Participant -> RailwayHTTP: POST /{session}/api/participant/location {lat,lon}
  RailwayHTTP -> ParticipantAPI: proxy precise location
  ParticipantAPI -> Host: notify_host(updated participant list)
end

alt Session id is stale or ended
  RailwayWS --> Participant: redirect + close (1008/1000)
end

note over RailwayWS
Participant actions now go through daemon REST endpoints.
The session WebSocket stays focused on presence, redirects, and broadcasts.
end note
@enduml
